  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given a valid CreateEventRequest, when POST /api/v1/events is called, then Event is created
      and 201 returned with EventDto.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given an Event is created, when Event Log is queried, then a "created" entry exists.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given an invalid request (missing required field), when POST is called, then 400 ProblemDetails
      is returned with field errors.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given a valid UpdateEventRequest, when PUT events/{id} is called, then Event is updated.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Integration tests pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    CreateEventRequest should include:
    - eventTypeId (required)
    - subject (required)
    - regardingEntityType, regardingRecordId (required)
    - startDate, endDate, dueDate, location, description (based on Event Type)

    Event Log entry format: action="created", previousStatus=null, newStatus="active"
  </notes>

